President Obama announced his intent to nominate several individuals to key Administration posts. Ariel Pablos-Méndez is nominated for Assistant Administrator for Global Health, USAID. Dr. Pablos-Méndez is currently Managing Director at The Rockefeller Foundation and Professor of Clinical Medicine and Epidemiology at Columbia University. Dan Arvizu is nominated for Member, National Science Board, National Science Foundation. He has served as Director and Chief Executive of the Department of Energy's National Renewable Energy Laboratory (NREL) and has extensive experience in the field of renewable energy. Alan Leshner is nominated for Member, National Science Board, National Science Foundation. He is the Chief Executive Officer of the American Association for the Advancement of Science and has held various positions in science and research organizations. Bob Granger is nominated for Member, Board of Directors of the National Board for Education Sciences. He is currently the President of the William T. Grant Foundation and has previously worked in education and research organizations. Leslie Fields and Roberta Ness are appointed as members of the Board of Directors of the Mickey Leland National Urban Air Toxics Research Committee. Frances Ulmer is appointed as Chair of the Arctic Research Commission. She is currently the Chancellor of the University of Alaska Anchorage and has held various positions in public policy and government.